&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bradley Unit- Neurorehabilitation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Specialist Neurophysiotherapist BAND 6 – Full time (37.5 hours per week)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;BASED AT Bradley Unit, Woking Community Hospital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;JOB ADVERT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available for a specialist neurophysiotherapist to join the Bradley Unit therapy team on a fixed term basis for 1 year. The Bradley unit is based at Woking Community Hospital. The successful candidate will work within the multidisciplinary team, providing high quality rehabilitation and support to service users in the subacute phase of their rehabilitation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Bradley Unit is a regional unit that specialises in neuro rehabilitation for patients with acquired brain injury, traumatic brain injury, Stroke, Multiple sclerosis and Guillain-Barre Syndrome. You will work closely with all other therapists and members of the MDT to provide an integrated care approach, working towards the patients’ individual goals from admission through to their discharge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The therapy teams at Ashford and St Peter’s Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust are integrated to enable therapists to work more closely with each other to improve patient care and experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role demands excellent clinical knowledge and application of neurorehabilitation skills to deliver high quality intervention. The caseload is complex and varied, with patients displaying a range of physical, cognitive and language impairments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexibility and good organisational and prioritisation skills are essential to this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated physiotherapist who is interested in developing their specialist skills in neurology and who will enjoy opportunities to be actively involved in the team and Trust’s service development. The successful candidate will have experience working in stroke rehabilitation and brain injury.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be fully supported by B7 team leaders. There is an established formal supervision and appraisal process and a robust in-house training programme, which provides opportunity to further develop your clinical and leadership skills to progress your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ashford and St Peter’s offers a seven day service across some specialities and you may be expected to support this on a rota system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Nicola Wilks, Clinical Lead for Inpatient Stroke and Neuro services on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;nicola.wilks2@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or Jenny Cheetham and Janine Graham on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;J.cheetham1@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; and JanineGraham1@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
